==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homogenesis
<hw>Ho`mo*gen"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets> + <ets>genesis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>That method of reproduction in which the successive generations are
alike, the offspring, either animal or plant, running through the same
cycle of existence as the parent; gamogenesis; -- opposed to
<xex>heterogenesis</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homogenetic</ent>⟦br⟧
